⊕meta⊕
name = "changelog-sky-workflow"
description = "Diff a .sky against its last committed git version and append a plain-English changelog entry to CHANGELOG.md."
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
max_budget_usd = 0.20
⊕⊕

※※
changelog-sky-workflow
======================
Produce a plain-English changelog entry for one .sky file by diffing its current
working-tree source against the last committed git version (HEAD), then append a
dated bullet to CHANGELOG.md in the same directory. Read-only on the .sky itself.

ASSUMES: --dir is inside a git-tracked working tree (uses `git diff HEAD`). If the
file has no uncommitted changes, the entry records "no changes" instead of failing.

DAG
---
  diff (bash: git diff HEAD for the file; emits a no-change marker if empty)
    |
    v
  describe (claude haiku: turn the diff into ONE reviewable changelog bullet)
    |
    v
  emit (bash: print the bullet, append it under a dated heading to CHANGELOG.md)

RUN
---
  sky run changelog-sky-workflow --vars dir=/path/to/repo,name=my-workflow

VARS
----
  dir   directory containing the .sky AND its CHANGELOG.md; must be a git working tree
  name  workflow filename without the .sky extension (the file diffed)
※※

※※
diff: git working-tree vs HEAD for the target .sky; emit a stable marker when there are no uncommitted changes.
※※
§diff§
bash = "set -u\nFILE=\"$SKY_NAME.sky\"\nif [ ! -f \"$SKY_DIR/$FILE\" ]; then echo \"error: $SKY_DIR/$FILE not found\" >&2; exit 1; fi\nif ! git -C \"$SKY_DIR\" rev-parse --git-dir >/dev/null 2>&1; then echo \"error: $SKY_DIR is not a git working tree\" >&2; exit 1; fi\nDIFF=$(git -C \"$SKY_DIR\" diff HEAD -- \"$FILE\" 2>/dev/null)\nif [ -z \"$DIFF\" ]; then echo \"NO_UNCOMMITTED_CHANGES\"; else printf '%s\\n' \"$DIFF\"; fi"
§§

※※
describe: read the diff from the upstream node and write ONE concise changelog bullet in reviewable prose.
※※
§describe§
model = "haiku"
depends_on = ["diff"]
§§

∆describe∆
You write changelog bullets for .sky workflow files.

The unified git diff (working tree vs HEAD) for the file {{name}}.sky is available
in the environment variable $SKY_OUTPUT_DIFF.

If $SKY_OUTPUT_DIFF is exactly the single token NO_UNCOMMITTED_CHANGES, output
exactly this one line and nothing else:

- no changes

Otherwise, read the diff and output EXACTLY ONE markdown bullet line (starting with
"- ") in plain English describing what changed. Focus on reviewable semantics:
added/removed/renamed nodes, changed depends_on or trigger_rule wiring, trigger
changes, budget (max_budget_usd) changes, model changes, and prompt or bash edits.
Be concise and specific. Do not quote raw diff lines. Do not add headings, code
fences, or any text other than the single bullet line.
∆∆

※※
emit: print the bullet, then append it under a dated heading to CHANGELOG.md in the target dir.
※※
§emit§
depends_on = ["describe"]
bash = "set -u\nBULLET=\"$SKY_OUTPUT_DESCRIBE\"\nLOG=\"$SKY_DIR/CHANGELOG.md\"\nDATE=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nif [ ! -f \"$LOG\" ]; then printf '# Changelog\\n' > \"$LOG\"; fi\nprintf '%s\\n' \"$BULLET\"\nprintf '\\n## %s - %s\\n%s\\n' \"$DATE\" \"$SKY_NAME\" \"$BULLET\" >> \"$LOG\"\necho \"appended entry for $SKY_NAME to $LOG\""
§§
